1️⃣ Initialize Git (if your folder isn’t a repo yet)
git init

2️⃣ Add your files to staging
git add .


. adds all files. You can also add specific files like git add file.txt.

3️⃣ Commit your changes
git commit -m "Your commit message"


Example:

git commit -m "Initial commit"

4️⃣ Add GitHub remote
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git


Replace username and repo with your GitHub username and repository name.
You only need to do this once per repository.

5️⃣ Push to GitHub
git push -u origin main


If your default branch is master instead of main, use master.
-u sets origin main as the default for future pushes.

6️⃣ Future changes

After making changes, you only need to do:

git add .
git commit -m "Update message"
git push